Add z-index to UI elements for improved layering and interaction
Ensures proper stacking of modals and panels by adding or adjusting `z-index` values. Fixes issues with element visibility and clickability in overlapping UI components. Removed redundant comments for cleaner code.

Update tutorial images for ingredients and oven
Updated the `ingredients-min.png` and `oven-min.png` images in the `public/tuto` directory. These changes ensure the tutorial visuals are up-to-date and consistent.

Add tutorial step for Orders UI functionality
Introduce a new tutorial entry explaining the Orders UI, detailing how to read incoming requests, required actions, and the timer bar. Added a corresponding image file for better user guidance.

Add tutorial step for held item UI with associated image
This update introduces a new tutorial step explaining the held item UI, helping users understand the bottom-center UI slots. Additionally, it includes the required 'held-item-min.png' image for the tutorial display.

div.div: While the demons were rising, mankind was about to become extinct. Six temples rose, and protected the last of mankind. A young boy joins the temple as a knight to save his mother. During his journey of wonders and mischief in the world of temples and demons, will he be able to ascend to become the strongest knight and inherit the throne?
The second season of Wu Dong Qiankun.

One big fat lie and a few twisted truths.
Even in his past life, Cid's dream wasn't to become a protagonist or a final boss. He'd rather lie low as a minor character until it's prime time to reveal he's a mastermind...or at least, do the next best thing-pretend to be one! And now that he's been reborn into another world, he's ready to set the perfect conditions to live out his dreams to the fullest. Armed with his overactive imagination, Cid jokingly recruits members to his organization and makes up a whole backstory about an evil cult that they need to take down. Well, as luck would have it, these imaginary adversaries turn out to be the real deal-and everyone knows the truth but him!
(Source: Yen Press)

Back then, Dok-Ja had no idea. He had no idea his favorite web novel 'Three Ways to Survive the Apocalypse' was going to come to life, and that he would become the only person to know how the world was going to end. He also had no idea he would end up becoming the protagonist of this novel-turned-reality. Now, Dok-Ja will go on a journey to change the course of the story and save humankind once and for all.
(Source: WEBTOONS, edited)
